column5: Well, headed out the door at 8:00am and went to the same spot i hit a few fish the morning before. Gave it a half an hour with nothing so decided to pack up and go for a little drive. After a little hike through the bush we arrived at the spot. fished for an hour and a half with nothing then i caught about 3 or so pound pike. Not two minutes after my buddy hits a 3.5lb rainbow, and about ten minutes after that i hit a nice rainbow gave me a good battle with the 6lb test and lots of logs near by. Packed it in shortly after that. With some fresh rainbow roe from the small female we kept this morning i decided to hit a spot for an hour before dinner,and ended getting another feisty little rainbow.
Nice shootin'. Those are very pretty fish.
Looks like you have yourself a good spot there. A pike and some good sized trout all from the same spot must be nice.
Great report and pics springbok  Real nice rainbows WTG Thanks for sharing Leechman
Some real purdy fish there!!!  Looks like it wasn't that cold in your nek of the woods either!
WTG springbok....you're getting a lot of those in the past few days, great to see the pics.
Very nice fish and thats a fat little Pike
Did the snot rocket take a roe bag ?
